Governor Simon Bako Lalong of Plateau state on Saturday delivered his polling unit at Ajikamai in Shendam local government area of Plateau state to President Muhammadu Buhari. The All Progressives Congress (APC) polled 1,166 against the Peoples Democratic Party’s (PDP) 66 for the Presidential elections. For Senate, the APC recorded 1,226 while the PDP polled 59 votes. Results for the House of Representatives saw the APC winning with 1,095 against the PDP’s 65 votes. 2019 Polls: Buhari humbles Atiku at Dankwambo's polling unit Mimiko wins polling unit as Atiku defeats Buhari Buhari wins in El-Rufai's polling unit